---
Source:
  - Title: A Year with Hafiz
    ISBN: 9780143117544
    Page: 144
Title: All Shape Would Collapse
Author: Hafiz
---
Your breathing draws me in and out.
All beings' joys and fears I share.
Something we call God I move with.
The holy spirit is my twin.
Without me all shape would collapse
It is true I hold you up.
Existence's cane is my love.
